{'text': 'This is probably one of the most important issues out there. \xa0We are living in a society that has been built around the fear of the unknown.'}
{'text': "Society isn't perfect. Society is imperfect because we are human. We have our bad moments, and sometimes we screw things up. \xa0The same goes for drugs. Drugs are bad."}
{'text': "Wouldn't it be better if marijuana was legal because no one was getting high? \xa0Maybe then there would be less of a social stigma around drugs."}
{'text': 'The current way our policy treats drug users is wrong. We need to treat drug users more humanely and give them a place in society.'}
{'text': 'Think about what kind of society we want to live in, and what kind of country we want to live in.'}
{'text': "I don't know why alcohol and cigarettes are still legal. I don't think there's a need to legalize drugs."}
{'text': 'I think the government will eventually be forced to legalize all drugs, especially if the rate of addiction to these substances continues to grow.'}
{'text': "I'm sure that there will be some people who will be attracted to the idea of legalized drugs, just like there are people who are attracted to all kinds of other illegal activities."}
{'text': "We wouldn't have to worry about protecting our kids from a drug-addicted parent anymore. It doesn't make sense to keep this sort of person from being able to access all sorts of drugs."}

{'text': "If we legalize drugs, then maybe we'll finally decide to stop criminalizing people for using them. Maybe then we'll finally come to realize that our drug laws are just another way to control people."}
{'text': 'The federal government will still have a role in the enforcement of the current drug laws. \xa0But it will no longer be the federal government. \xa0The DEA will still be around.'}
{'text': 'Legalization can be a good thing, but we should make sure to regulate it properly.'}
{'text': 'If you want to legalize drugs, make sure you have lots of controls on how the drugs are being distributed, sold, and used.'}
{'text': "It's ludicrous to say that drugs are inherently evil. \xa0They are everywhere, and everyone has access to them."}
{'text': "Isn't it exactly the same as what happened with alcohol in the 20's and 30's when people started drinking and smoking cigarettes?"}
{'text': "If we legalize all drugs, how are we going to prevent people from using drugs? We can't arrest them all. \xa0We can't imprison them all."}
{'text': 'There are plenty of dangerous drugs out there.'}
{'text': 'If you want to consume drugs in moderation, I think it might be easier to avoid the law entirely.'}
{'text': "Just legalize all drugs. \xa0There's no sense in keeping it illegal. \xa0Just legalize everything, as if it were as simple as that. Just legalize all drugs."}
{'text': 'I think that if we legalized drugs, we would lose sight of the main reason why these drugs are illegal in the first place. \xa0Drugs are illegal because they are harmful to others.'}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you'll increase the amount of people who are dependent on drugs. \xa0This will lead to more drug-related crime, violence, and other issues."}
{'text': "Legalizing drugs is absolutely not going to solve the drug problem. \xa0It's obviously not going to be the best solution, but it's certainly not going to be the worst solution either."}
{'text': "Of course, I don't support any plans that involve decriminalization of drugs. \xa0That's just not my thing. \xa0However, I do support legalizing drugs for recreational use."}
{'text': 'To me, this means that we will have less and less problems with drugs, because everyone will have access to them. \xa0I think that would be a good thing.'}
{'text': "There are plenty of other ways to handle the drug problem that don't involve legalizing drugs."}
{'text': "Legalizing drugs would be the biggest mistake in the history of humanity. \xa0We'd never be able to go back."}
{'text': "I don't think it's necessary to deal with the drug problem in the first place. The drug problem has been around for a very long time. \xa0It's not going to go away."}
{'text': "In the future, if people can get drugs without getting caught, they'll be more likely to take them. I don't see how that's a bad thing."}
{'text': "If you want to talk about how to handle the drug problem, don't ignore the real issue."}
{'text': 'Why would we legalize drugs? \xa0What makes it good to legalize drugs? Why would it be a good idea to legalize drugs?'}
{'text': "If cannabis is legal, it's never going to be used as a recreational drug. \xa0That would be ridiculous. \xa0It's not gonna be legal, so who's gonna buy it?"}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you'll have to deal with an insane public health care system that has failed miserably over the last few decades."}
{'text': 'Why do we even need to legalize drugs? \xa0Do we really have the right to do that?'}
{'text': 'The solution to the "drug problem is not to legalize drugs, but to legalize all drugs.'}
{'text': 'The majority of people who use drugs are not addicts. \xa0These people are simply trying to find something to offset the withdrawal symptoms they are feeling from their drug of choice.'}
{'text': 'We need to be honest with ourselves. \xa0We need to look at our current situation and tell ourselves that our current drug policies are not going to curb the use of these drugs.'}
{'text': "Why haven't we legalized drugs already? \xa0It's obviously a bad idea to be so hard on people for using drugs, but why haven't we already legalized alcohol?"}

{'text': 'There are many things we should be doing instead of legalizing drugs. We should be spending more money on rehabilitation programs for alcoholics. We should be funding more mental health research into addiction.'}
{'text': "There's no point to legalizing drugs if we're not going to make use of them. \xa0If we don't make use of them, they'll just remain illegal."}
{'text': "If we were to legalize drugs, we'd be setting ourselves up for problems like we've seen in Canada. \xa0I don't think we'd be able to effectively regulate such a massive market."}
{'text': 'Look at how much of a mess the liquor industry is right now. \xa0The illegal alcohol industry is probably bigger than the legal alcoholic beverage industry.'}
